channel.title: How do I change ip adress on Hybrid-PvP source?
channel.description: Hello, how do I change ip adress on the hybrid-pvp source? .. I've tried to search for 0.0.0 in client.java but can't find anything.. hosting it on localhost so there has to be a localhost adress somewere in the files, right?

item.title: How do I change ip adress on Hybrid-PvP source?
item.dc:creator: @dillktm65 dillktm65
item.description:
@dillktm65 wrote:

[quote=“PriMaL_PvP, post:15, topic:393981”][quote author=master laake link=topic=491165.msg3659135#msg3659135 date=1310239961]
ricliv, im having the same problem! and these other retards are trying to tell us to change client sided shit, when we need server side ip places to be changed for it to become a public server. aka through a webclient. the one in source that is 0.0.0.0 is just to change the text, and ive gone trhough the server and client.java files SERVER sided and havent found anything so there has to be a hidden file somewhere that the other files read from! so these other guys telling us to change client sided they are fucking retarted and dont know shit about getting server sided public!!!1
[/quote]
Your 1 Big Idiot.[/quote]

Agreed. I thought you had to just go to client.java in the client folder, and search for “Server =” then put your server IP after the “Server =”, No source IP need’s changing.
